==Marketing and release==

The teaser poster of ''Kaminey'' was received positively by critics.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bollywood's best posters of 2009|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/dec/15/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-posters-of-2009.htm#5|author=Sen, Raja|publisher=Rediff.com|date=15 December 2009|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref> The trailer, which introduces four characters; one lisping, one stuttering, a woman yelling about having raped a man and one jeering at the lisper, received positive reviews.<ref name="trailer">{{cite web|title=The best trailers of 2009|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/slide-show-1-the-best-trailers-of-2009/20091209.htm#8|author=Sen, Raja|publisher=Rediff.com|date=9 December 2009|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref> Critics kept their expectations high due to Bhardwaj's previous films, and said the trailer was like a comic book which introduces the characters of Kapoor and Chopra differently.<ref name="trailer"/> The theatrical trailers and the music generated interest for the film.<ref name="hard work"/> The film's marketing also involved public appearances by Chopra and Kapoor.<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka-Shahid promote Kaminey|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-08-14/news-interviews/28161709_1_kaminey-priyanka-and-shahid-theatres|work=The Times of India|date=14 August 2009|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref>

The makers of the film were disappointed by the [[Central Board of Film Certification|Censor Board for Film Certification]]'s decision to grant the film an "[[Central Board of Film Certification#Rating System|A]]" certificate{{mdash}}meant for viewers 18 years or older{{mdash}}instead of a "[[Central Board of Film Certification#Rating System|U/A]]" certificate that they had expected. Bhardwaj said, "It was injustice to us. There is no abusive language used in the film and the violence is of 'comic book kind'." The Censor Board asked him to replace dialogue which mentioned the city of [[Pilibhit]]{{mdash}}which they said was a sensitive constituency{{mdash}}with a fictitious city name. He replaced Pilibhit with Barabanki."<ref>{{cite news|title=Vishal unhappy over 'A' certificate to 'Kaminey'|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/vishal-unhappy-over-a-certificate-to-kaminey/499277|work=The Financial Express|date=7 August 2009|accessdate=21 August 2009}}</ref> The film was subject to some controversies. A [[First Information Report]] was filed by Jagannath Sena Sangathan at a police station in [[Puri]] against the film for allegedly denigrating [[Lord Jagannath]]. According to them, a scene in which the text "Apna Hath Jagannath" is seen in a toilet on a semi-clad model had hurt religious sentiments. The objectionable portion of the scene was removed from the prints released in the state of Orissa.<ref>{{cite web|title=FIR filed against Kaminey director, producer|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/Entertainment/FIR-filed-against-Kaminey-director-producer/Article1-446827.aspx|author=Indo-Asain News Service|work=Hindustan Times|date=25 August 2009|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref> A complaint supported by a caste group backed by a [[Samajwadi Party]] MP about the use of the name of a community "teli" in the song "Dhan Te Nan"{{mdash}}which was considered derogatory to the Teli community{{mdash}}was filed with the [[Ministry of Information and Broadcasting]]. The Censor Board reacted to the complaint, insisting on the replacement of the word, which was later replaced with "Dilli".<ref>{{cite web|title=Dhan te nan offensive to caste, so lyrics of Kaminey hit changed|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/dhan-te-nan-offensive-to-caste-so-lyrics-of-kaminey-hit-changed/518139/|author=Vishnoi, Anubhuti|work=The Indian Express|date=17 December 2009|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref>

''Kaminey'' was scheduled to release on 5 June 2009. However, the release was postponed because of problems between the producers and multiplexes in India.<ref name="sifyrole">{{cite web|title=Priyanka's Kaminey role to cause a stir|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/priyanka-s-kaminey-role-to-cause-a-stir-news-bollywood-kkfsa0aeeje.html|author=Indo-Asian News Service|publisher=Sify|date=9 May 2009|accessdate=17 June 2013}}</ref> The film was released on 14 August 2009 on 1,200 screens worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|title='Kaminey' not to release in Mumbai due to swine flu scare|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/kaminey-not-to-release-in-mumbai-due-to-swine-flu-scare_37959.htm|publisher=Zee News|date=12 August 2009|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref><ref name="tfe">{{cite web|title=Flu: Mumbai multiplexes to lose Rs 35 cr|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/flu-mumbai-multiplexes-to-lose-rs-35-cr/501305|author=Akhouri, Priyanka|work=The Financial Express|date=13 August 2009|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref> Because of the [[2009 flu pandemic in India|2009 flu pandemic]], the film was not released in the Maharashtra region{{mdash}}including Mumbai and Pune{{mdash}}because the multiplexes in these cities were closed by the Maharashtra government for three days as part of precautionary measures against swine flu.<ref name="tfe"/> [[Moser Baer|Moser Baer Home Videos]] released ''Kaminey'' on DVD in October 2009 across all regions in a two-disc pack complying with the [[NTSC]] format. One disc contains the film; the other has additional content including a "making of the film" documentary, the original beginning and deleted scenes.<ref name="DVD">{{cite web|title=Kaminey Review|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/dvdreview/13940/index.html|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20111203135554/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/dvdreview/13940/index.html|archivedate=3 December 2011|accessdate=14 February 2012}}</ref> [[VCD]] and [[Blu-Ray]] versions were released at the same time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey|url=http://www.boxofficeboss.in/title-detail.php?url_slug=&titleid=6857|publisher=[[Moser Baer|Box Office Boss]]|accessdate=17 June 2013}}</ref> Bollywood Hungama critic Joginder Tuteja rated the DVD 4 out of 5, praising the bonus features and the packaging.<ref name="DVD"/>

[[Airtel Digital TV]] premi<U+00E8>red the film on its Pay Per View service on 12 September 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=Airtel digital TV premieres Kaminey on PPV|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/press-releases/airtel-digital-tv-premieres-kaminey-on-ppv-109091000099_1.html|work=Business Standard|date=10 September 2009|accessdate=17 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141120070821/http://www.business-standard.com/article/press-releases/airtel-digital-tv-premieres-kaminey-on-ppv-109091000099_1.html|archivedate=20 November 2014}}</ref> The Indian television premi<U+00E8>re of the film was on [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]] on 28 February 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-zee-tv-ratings-soar-this-week-1359349 | title='Zee TV' ratings soar this week | publisher=DNA India | date=15 March 2010 | accessdate=19 November 2014}}</ref>

==Critical reception==

''Kaminey'' received unanimously positive reviews from critics who praised every aspect of the film. Raja Sen of Rediff.com rated the film 4.5 out of 5 and wrote, "''Kaminey'' is startlingly clever, an innovative film with genuine surprises. A kind of film whose success we ought all pray for, because it'll prove smart cinema works."<ref name="rs"/> ''[[The Indian Express]]'' gave a rating of 4 out of 5, calling it "Bollywood's first all-the-way-out-to-there pulp fiction".<ref name="tie"/> [[Rajeev Masand]] of [[CNN-IBN]] gave the film 4 stars out of 5, called it a "must watch" and wrote, "[i]t's an unpredictable crime drama that combines violence and dark humor in a manner that's reminiscent of the films of Quentin Tarantino, Guy Ritchie and the Coen Brothers. And yet Kaminey is so original and inventive in the manner in which it takes Bollywood's favorite formula{{mdash}}twin brothers{{mdash}}and turns it on its head." He praised the writing{{mdash}}which he said was the film's real strength, the non-linear screenplay and the dialogue, and wrote that the film has "the best performance you will see by an ensemble cast in a long time".<ref name="cnn"/> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] from ''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film 4 out of 5, and said it is "Bollywood's first film which is full of brains, brawn and belligerence besides being a bravura attempt to rewrite the tried and tested idiom of desi movielore. Kaminey is a smart and balsy film that brings Hollywood to Bollywood which catapult the viewer into the dark, violent world of crime and criminals, leaving you no time to blink or breathe easy&nbsp;...&nbsp;Tarantino, take a bow. Brave new Bollywood is here."<ref name="toir"/>

[[Anupama Chopra]] gave a rating of 4 out of 5 and wrote "Kaminey is the best Bollywood film I've seen this year. It's an audacious, original rollercoaster ride. Written and directed by Vishal Bharadwaj, Kaminey requires patience and attention but the pay off is more than worth it."<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Review|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/kaminey-416|author=Chopra, Anupama|publisher=[[NDTV]]|date=14 August 2009|accessdate=20 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141120072326/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/kaminey-416|archivedate=20 November 2014}}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of [[Bollywood Hungama]] rated the film 4 out of 5 and wrote "Kaminey is bold, stark, funny and unpredictable and is a film with an attitude. Like it or leave it, but you'd never be able to ignore it. Word from the wise: Go for this hatke (different) experience!"<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Review|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13940/index.html|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20100706045012/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13940/index.html|archivedate=6 July 2010|accessdate=14 February 2012}}</ref> [[Zee News]] also rated the film 4 out of 5 and said, "Bhardwaj has once again delivered a powerful film that completely bowls you over with its splendid script, riveting narrative and stellar performances by lead pair{{mdash}}Shahid and Priyanka [who] have a cracking on-screen chemistry that certainly reminds you of yesteryears {{sic}} on-screen couples." The review also said, "''Kaminey'' is an engrossing flick that does not let you move from your seat!"<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: <U+2018>Kaminey<U+2019> bowls you over with its power packed performance!|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/review-kaminey-bowls-you-over-with-its-power-packed-performance_38127.htm|publisher=[[Zee News]]|date=14 August 2009|accessdate=29 May 2013}}</ref> Kaveree Bamzai of ''[[India Today]]'' rated the film 4 out of 5 and said it "is dark, melodramatic, poetic and ultimately operatic". He also said, "Its lyrics are the blow-up-your-brains-out kind&nbsp;...&nbsp;and its music, composed by the multi-talented Bharadwaj is perfectly in sync with a narrative that doesn't pause for breath."<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey: Mumbai, on speed|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Kaminey:+Mumbai,+on+speed/1/56601.html|author=Bamzai, Kaveree|work=[[India Today]]|date=13 August 2009|accessdate=29 May 2013}}</ref> Namrata Joshi from ''Outlook'' gave a rating of 4 out 5 and called ''Kaminey'' "a strikingly anarchic, unusually energetic, quirky and frenetic film".<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Review|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/story.aspx?sid=4&aid=261431|author=Joshi, Namrata|work=[[Outlook (magazine)|Outlook]]|date=18 August 2009|accessdate=29 May 2013}}</ref> [[Sudhish Kamath]] of ''[[The Hindu]]'' gave the film 4 stars and wrote, "Kaminey takes the post-postmodern noir genre to a whole new level, to a sophistication the Indian audience isn't used to. Watch it at least twice to fully appreciate this masterpiece."<ref>{{cite web|title=Sons of guns have a blast|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/sons-of-guns-have-a-blast/article3026.ece|author=Kamath, Sudhish|work=The Hindu|date=|accessdate=4 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kamath|first1=Sudhish|title=Kaminey: What he did to Shakespeare, Vishal Bhardwaj now does to Ritchie, Tarantino & the Coens. Deja vu Ek chalis ki last local. 4 stars.|url=https://twitter.com/SudhishKamath/status/3293123474|website=Twitter|accessdate=12 August 2014}}</ref>

==Box office==

With unanimously positive reviews, ''Kaminey'' was successful throughout India, with occupancy around 90% across multiplexes. The film was successful across most single screens,<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Gets Big Opening Life Partner Below The Mark|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1090&nCat=box_office_report|publisher=Box Office India|date=15 August 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130926193527/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1090&nCat=box_office_report|archivedate=26 September 2013}}</ref> and collected {{INRConvert|170|m|nolink=yes}} in India during the opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey nets Rs 170 mn; Life Partner Rs 62.5 million in India|url=http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/kaminey-nets-rs-170-mn-life-partner-rs-625-million-in-india/29088|author=Adesara, Hetal|publisher=Business of Cinema|date=17 August 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141120073650/http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/kaminey-nets-rs-170-mn-life-partner-rs-625-million-in-india/29088|archivedate=20 November 2014}}</ref> In its first week of release, the film collected {{INRConvert|250|m|nolink=yes}} in India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sikandar And Shadow Poor Kaminey Has Good First Week|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1113&nCat=box_office_report|publisher=Box Office India|date=22 August 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130926193519/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1113&nCat=box_office_report|archivedate=26 September 2013}}</ref> Because of the delayed release in Maharashtra, it lost about {{INRConvert|50|m|nolink=yes}}. However, the film profited in Mumbai after its release in Maharashtra on Monday and during its run, and it had earned {{INRConvert|410|m|nolink=yes}} within four weeks.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey beats the flu, tops box office|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=14905271&cid=14521781|publisher=Sify|date=18 August 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Another Dull Week For New Releases|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1132&nCat=box_office_report|publisher=Box Office India|date=12 September 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130926193522/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1132&nCat=box_office_report|archivedate=26 September 2013}}</ref> ''Kaminey'' earned {{INRConvert|710|m|nolink=yes}} worldwide; [[Box Office India]] declared it a hit and it became a commercial success.<ref name="Lifetime Worldwide"/>

Overseas, the film grossed around {{INRConvert|82.50|m|nolink=yes}} in North America, the UAE, the UK and Australia during the opening weekend. The film's most successful overseas market was North America.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Good Life Partner Poor in International Markets|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1103&nCat=overseas_report|publisher=Box Office India|date=18 August 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130926193525/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1103&nCat=overseas_report|archivedate=26 September 2013}}</ref> It collected around {{INRConvert|120|m|nolink=yes}} in 10 days from international markets and proved to be a commercial success outside India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Above Average Life Partner Flop|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1117&nCat=overseas_report|publisher=Box Office India|date=25 August 2009|accessdate=3 June 2013|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130926193530/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=1117&nCat=overseas_report|archivedate=26 September 2013}}</ref>

==Legacy==
Award-winning director [[Shekhar Kapur]] praised the film, saying, "Kaminey catapults Indian Cinema in modernity beyond Tarantino".<ref>{{cite web|title='Kaminey' takes Indian cinema beyond Tarantino, says Shekhar Kapur|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/kaminey-takes-indian-cinema-beyond-tarantino-says-shekhar-kapur_38954.htm|author=Indo-Asian News Service|publisher=Zee News|date=23 August 2009|accessdate=29 May 2013}}</ref> He said that ''Kaminey'' would be able to compete with any film in the world in terms of its design, performances, inherent narratives, editing and pace.<ref name="real"/> Notable filmmaker and two times [[Filmfare Award]] winner [[Karan Johar]] labelled it a cult film, describing it as "edgy&nbsp;...&nbsp;cult and geniusely performed and executed! Go get a shot of new age cinema and cinematic bravery!"<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey is a cult film: Karan Johar|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-08-18/news-interviews/28190976_1_kaminey-fimply-fuperb-priyanka-chopra|work=The Times of India|date=18 August 2009|accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref> The film became the most widely debated and dissected Bollywood film after [[Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra]]'s 2006 film ''[[Rang De Basanti]]''.<ref name="outlook"/> Several critics and media publication placed the film at number one on their "Best film of the year" lists.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rajeev Masand's Hits & Pits of 2009|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/rajeev-masands-hits--pits-of-2009/107735-8.html|author=Masand, Rajeev|publisher=CNN-IBN|date=26 December 2013|accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Best Films of 2009|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/dec/28/slide-show-1-best-film-of-2009.htm#9|author=Sen, Raja|publisher=Rediff.com|date=28 December 2009|accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref> Raja Sen said the performances were among the best performances of 2009. Gupte, Roy Sanyal and Kapoor were placed at numbers six, three and one respectively as the best performances of 2009 by a Hindi actor.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Actors of 2009|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/dec/30/slide-show-1-best-actors-of-2009.htm#9|author=Sen, Raja|publisher=Rediff.com|date=31 December 2009|accessdate=15 June 2013}}</ref>

Chopra was placed at number one as the best performance of 2009 by an Hindi actress.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Actresses of 2009|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/dec/31/slide-show-1-best-actresses-of-2009.htm#9|author=Sen, Raja|publisher=Rediff.com|date=31 December 2009|accessdate=15 June 2013}}</ref> Chopra said, "[y]ou don't get to work in a fantastic movie like ''Kaminey'' and play someone like Sweety every day".<ref name="sifyrole"/> Hindi Film News said ''Kaminey'' was the best Bollywood film of the decade.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Bollywood Movie of the Last Decade (2000<U+2013>2009)|url=http://www.hindifilmnews.com/bollywood_buzz/poll-best-bollywood-movie-of-the-last-decade-2000-2009/#.UPUbw-jrN84|publisher=Hindi Film News}}</ref> It ranked Shahid Kapoor's performance at number four for the finest performance by a Bollywood actor for the decade, and in a public poll the song "Dhan Te Nan" was voted the thirteenth-best Bollywood song of the decade.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Finest Performance of a Bollywood Actor in the Last Decade (2001<U+2013>2010) |url=http://www.hindifilmnews.com/polls-2/poll-5-the-finest-performance-of-a-bollywood-actor-in-the-last-decade-2001-2010/#.UPUcsujrN84 |publisher=Hindi Film News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Best Hindi Film (Bollywood) Song of the Decade (2001<U+2013>2010)|url=http://www.hindifilmnews.com/polls-2/poll-8-the-best-hindi-film-bollywood-song-of-the-decade-2000-2010/|publisher=Hindi Film News}}</ref> Rediff.com included the film on its list of "Top 25 Hindi Action Films of all Time".<ref>{{cite web|title=The Top 25 Hindi Action Films of all Time|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-the-top-25-hindi-action-films-of-all-time/20120127.htm#15|author=Sen, Raja|publisher=Rediff.com|date=27 January 2012|accessdate=15 June 2013}}</ref> Since its release, the film has gained a cult following and is regarded as a [[cult film]] of the 2000s decade of Bollywood.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shahid-Priyanka's Kaminey sequel very much on cards|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Shahid-Priyanka-s-Kaminey-sequel-very-much-on-cards/Article1-987339.aspx|author=Press Trust of India|work=Hindustan Times|date=9 January 2013|accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref>

==Awards and nominations==
''Kaminey'' has received several awards and nominations in categories ranging from recognition of the film itself, to its cinematography, direction, screenplay, music and cast performances. At the [[55th Filmfare Awards]], the film received ten nominations{{mdash}}more than any other film{{mdash}}for awards including Best Film, director, Actor and Actress. However, it won only the award for [[Filmfare Award for Best Special Effects|Best Special Effects]]. The film also won two [[National Film Awards (India)|National Film Awards]]; [[National Film Award for Best Audiography|Best Audiography]] for Subash Sahoo and [[National Film Award <U+2013> Special Jury Award / Special Mention (Feature Film)|Special Jury Award]] for Film Editing at the [[57th National Film Awards]] for [[A. Sreekar Prasad]]. It received eleven nominations at the 5th [[Apsara Film & Television Producers Guild Award]] and won two, one of which was [[Apsara Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role|Best Actress]] for Chopra.
